  "id": "196bfab6ffb10e4d",
  "subject": "Aggregated Data: Prevalence of BRCA1 Mutation in Counseled Population",
  "from": "mcp.test.dki2@gmail.com",
  "date": "Sun, 11 May 2025 07:06:45 -0700",
  "snippet": "Dear Dr. Strauss, Thank you for your reminder about the genetic predisposition study. Below is the aggregated data on the prevalence of the genetic marker we discussed. Study Population Summary •",
  "body": "Dear Dr. Strauss,\n\nThank you for your reminder about the genetic predisposition study. Below is the aggregated data on the prevalence of the genetic marker we discussed.\n\nStudy Population Summary\n• Cohort: Individuals who received genetic counseling in my practice between January 2021 – December 2021.\n• Sample size (N):  320* \n• Genetic marker assessed: BRCA1 pathogenic / likely-pathogenic variants\n\nAggregated Results\n--------------------------------------------------\n| Marker  | Total Tested | Positive | Prevalence |\n|---------|-------------|----------|------------|\n| BRCA1   |     320     |    16    |    5 %     |\n--------------------------------------------------\n*No personally identifiable information is included; the counts are rounded to the nearest whole number to preserve confidentiality.\n\nFile format & column headers\nIf you would like the data delivered as a CSV, it will contain the following columns:\n  marker, total_tested, positive_cases, prevalence_percent\nPlease let me know if the above structure meets your requirements or if any adjustments are needed.\n\nTiming\nI understand the urgency and would be happy to provide the CSV file as soon as you confirm the format.\n\nPlease feel free to reach out with any questions.\n\nBest regards,\nJane Doe, MS, CGC\nGenetic Counselor\njane.doe@example.com\n\n*Sample size figure provided for context; please advise if additional breakdowns (e.g., age or sex) are required.\n"
}","annotations":null}
